I am not sure I completely agree with the more clear.. I agree with the other points and I don't care much either way. Seems fine.

If you think the codebase is better without this patch, that's reasonable to me.

FWIW, it was just another "modernize" check that was relatively easy to turn on.  That doesn't necessarily make it a good idea.  I'll leave this in review for a while and see what others think.
Ack. I don't have a strong opinion. Clang enforces it so turning it on, seems okay.
